h the scaled solar term and a modified Lorentzian function also\nmatch the three cooler simulations reasonably well. ... Our simplified results\nsuggest that the surface effect is generally larger in hotter stars (and\ncorrespondingly smaller in cooler stars) and of similar shape in stars of solar\ntype and cooler. However, we cannot presently predict whether this will remain\nso when other components of the surface effect are included.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 8 Jun 2016 20:00:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-08-31"}
