 processed by hydrogen\nburning, coming from a massive star experiencing mild-to-strong rotational\nmixing. During its burning, this material was likely enriched in helium burning\nproducts. No material coming from the carbon-oxygen rich core of the source\nstar should be added to form the daughter star, otherwise the $^{12}$C/$^{13}$C\nratio would be largely above the observed range of values.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 8 Jun 2016 20:47:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-07"}
