 $L_b$\nand the total energy in the electromagnetic channel $E_{\\rm total}$) of SGRBs,\nand find that while equally well reproducing other observational constraints,\nQS EoSs predict a much narrower $t_b$ distribution than that of the NS EoSs,\nbetter matching the data. We therefore suggest that the post-merger product of\nNS-NS mergers might be fast-rotating supramassive QSs rather than NSs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 9 Jun 2016 12:36:43 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 18 Oct 2016 04:21:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-11-02"}
